!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

description /dɪˈskrɪpʃən/

(descriptions) 

1. N-VAR A description of someone or something is an account which explains what they are or what they look like. 描述 

例： Police have issued a description of the man who was aged between fifty and sixty. 警方已已公布了这一年龄在50至60之间的男子的相貌特征。 

例： The paper provides a detailed description of how to create human embryos by cloning. 这篇论文对如何通过克隆制造人类胚胎提供详细的描述。 

2. N-SING If something is of a particular description , it belongs to the general class of items that are mentioned. 属…种类 

例： Events of this description occurred daily. 这类事件每天都有发生。 

3. N-UNCOUNT You can say that something is beyond description , or that it defies description , to emphasize that it is very unusual, impressive, terrible, or extreme. 无法形容 [强调] 

例： His face is weary beyond description. 他脸上的疲惫无法形容。

</div>

